      "Hierarchy: Collection -> Document -> Fields. A 'collection' below ~= a table; a 'document' ~= a row; a 'field' ~= a column.",
      "Subcollections are nested under a parent document path, e.g. companies/{companyId}/listings/{listingId}.",
      "'Relationships' are by stored ID strings (path references), enforced in application code, not by the database.",
      "Many fields are denormalized (copied) for read performance, e.g. listing.assignedEmployeeName duplicates the employee's name.",
